<div class="row" id="accounting">
  <div class="col-sm-12">
    <h1>Accounting</h1>
  </div>
  <div class="col-sm-4 col-sm-offset-1">
    <div class="left-header">
      <h2>Monthly Financials</h2>
    </div>
      <p>Never wait until tax time again--you deserve to know <strong>now</strong>
        how you're doing.</p>
      <p>Every month, we work through a detailed checklist in concert
        with you--CEOs, Project Managers, owners and founders--to arrive at
        accurate, timely finanical statements. We go beyond the standard
        reconciliations, and diligently guide and teach the methods needed for
        financials in a contracting environment. Revised estimates, WIP accounting
        and a true understanding of change orders are all a part of our job</p>
      <p>We offer a simple guarentee--you receive your monthly finanicals by the
        end of the following month, or we don't get paid. Simple as that.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="col-sm-4 col-sm-offset-1">
    <div class="left-header">
      <h2>Weekly Reporting</h2>
    </div>
    <p> Every client has different numbers that mean something to them. You have
      your own--possibly it's sales related, possibly it's operation related--but
      part of our job is to help you find those numbers, and give you an opportunity
      to discover the patterns in them.</p>
    <p> We build a scorecard, and as part of our weekly meetings, we look at the
      numbers together. With the help of your whole team, we change last week
      from a mystery to a certainty, from a blur of work to a clarity of digits.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="col-sm-6 col-sm-offset-3">
    <div class="left-header">
      <h2>Strategic Forecasting</h2>
    </div>
    <p>In contracting, there's often a question that seems to defy understanding: If all my
      jobs are profitable, how is it possible that I'm losing money?</p>
    <p>We take that concern seriously. Together with those responsible for
      spending the money, we create a strategic forecast. This forecast becomes
      our measuring stick--<i>I thought I was going to spend $1000 all year on utilities;
      it's only June and I've spent $1500</i>--and we revisit it throughout the year
      to help you better understand where your job profits are being spent.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="row" id="tools">
  <div class="col-sm-12">
    <h1>Tools</h1>
  </div>
  <div class="col-sm-4 col-sm-offset-1">
    <div class="left-header-blue">
      <h2> Silvertime</h2>
    </div>
    <p>Time keeping is a critical part of every contracting company. First, in
      order to control labor costs, time must be tracked to a job. Second, time
      spent on many jobs is directly billable, and it must be tracked accurately
      so your customers are willing to pay.</p>
    <p>The problem was that we counldn't find the right mixture in the timecard
      systems that were commercially available, so we built our own, and christianed
      it <strong>Silvertime</strong>.</p>
    <p>With Silvertime, an employee is able to quickly and easily track their
      own time, and a foreman or owner has a simple method for reviewing
      and approving that time. All the data is availble to the right people at the
      right time</p>
  </div>
  <div class="col-sm-4 col-sm-offset-1">
    <div class="left-header-blue">
      <h2>ComputerEase</h2>
    </div>
    <p>The right choice of an accounting system is important, and we decided
      to use an oldie but a goodie. ComputerEase has all the right mixture of
      excellent job-costing tools and ease of use that is required to manage
      both individual jobs and whole contracting companies well.</p>
    <p> We use all the modules to bring you accurate results--Job Cost, Accounts
      Payable, Equipment, Payroll, etc--and you never have to worry about upgrades,
      support, or servers.</p>
    <p></p>
  </div>
</div>

